			Sentiment detection of tweets is one of the basicanalysis utility functions needed by various applications over twitter data.
			Many systems and ap proaches have been implemented to automatically detect sentiment on texts (e.g., news articles, Web reviews and Web blogs) (Pang et al, 2002; Pang and Lee, 2004; Wiebe and Riloff, 2005; Glance et al, 2005; Wilson et al, 2005).
			Most of theseapproaches use the raw word representation (n grams) as features to build a model for sentiment detection and perform this task over large pieces of texts.
			However, the main limitation of usingthese techniques for the Twitter context is mes sages posted on Twitter, so-called tweets, are veryshort.
			The maximum size of a tweet is 140 char acters.
